text: the examination is essentially similar to the prior study with considerable thickening in the left maxillary sinus and probable air-fluid levels with moderate polypoid thickening of the right maxillary sinus, considerable opacification of the central ethmoid cells and some soft tissue thickening on the right side of the sphenoid sinus.the sphenoid sinus thickening is, however, slightly more extensive than the previous exam.
summary: some increased sphenoid sinus thickening.otherwise, stable appearance of the sinuses with considerable soft tissue opacification as described.

text: there are no air-fluid levels in the paranasal sinuses.there is mild mucosal thickening in the maxillary sinuses bilaterally.there is minimal mucosal thickening in some of the ethmoid air cells bilaterally.there is a mucus retention cyst in a left ethmoid air cell.there is another mucus retention cyst in the right sphenoid sinus.the visualized osseous structures appear unremarkable.
summary: no evidence of acute or active sinusitis.

text: there is a hypoplastic left frontal sinus.there is a polyp vs.mucosal retention cyst in the right maxillary sinus.there is mucosal thickening within the ethmoid air cells bilaterally and the right maxillary sinus.there is opacification and an air fluid level within the left maxillary sinus.there are bilateral ___ bullosa.there is no evidence of bone destruction.the material within the sinuses is not of increased density to indicate hemorrhage.the sphenoid sinuses are clear.the right frontal sinus is clear.

text: there are facial bone fractures involving the lateral wall of the right orbit, where the fracture is comminuted.the fracture planes extend posteriorly into the sphenoid ___.there are also fractures involving the frontal bones bilaterally, extending superiorly out of the plane of view on the left.the fractures are noted to be comminuted in the left frontal bone region and pneumocephalus is noted in the subdural space in this region.this may relate to the patient's craniotomy.the maxilla and mandible are intact.there are air-fluid levels throughout the paranasal sinuses.
summary: multiple bilateral fractures as described but more notable on the right, where the lateral wall of the orbit and the sphenoid ___ and skull base are involved.

text: there is mucosal thickening and fluid within bilateral maxillary sinuses.the right maxillary sinus is almost completely obscured.there is also almost-complete opacification of the ethmoid air cells.the frontal air cells are under-developed but are clear.the sphenoid air cells are completely opacified.prominent superior opthalmic veins noted bilaterally, of unknown clinical significance.the coronal images show the nasal septum grossly midline with a left-sided bony spur.the mucosa of the osteomeatal complexes are thickened and obstructed.the right cribriform plate is approximately 2 mm higher than the left.the lamina papyracea is intact.the surrounding bones show no evidence of bony destruction.the anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.
summary: interval increase in pan-sinus inflammatory disease as described above.

text: in comparison to the prior ct of the head performed ___, there has been an interval decrease in the amount of diffuse opacification of the imaged superior ethmoid air cells and bilateral maxillary sinuses.on the current study, there is mild residual mucosal thickening within the inferior portions of the maxillary sinuses and moderate circumferential mucosal thickening within the sphenoid sinus.multiple fracture lines extending through the pterygoid plates and the right maxillary sinus are re-demonstrated.
summary: interval decrease in sinus opacification, with some residual opacification of the maxillary sinuses.sphenoid sinus moderate opacification cannot be compared to the prior study as this region was not covered previously.

text: the contents of the orbits appear normal.the frontal, ethmoid and sphenoid sinuses are without mucosal thickening.minimal dependent fluid is seen within the maxillary sinuses.the ostiomeatal units are patent bilaterally.the cribriform plates are parallel.there is deformity of the nasal bones, suggesting prior fracture of these structures.incidental note is made of a large torus palatinus.extensive periodontal and periapical lucencies are seen within the superior alveolar ridge of the maxilla on both sides, consistent with periapical cysts or abscesses.
summary: minimal dependent maxillary sinus fluid, without evidence of significant drainage obstruction.extensive periodontal and periapical disease.correlation with dental evaluation is advised.

text: there are air-fluid levels within bilateral maxillary sinuses.an external catheter is seen entering the left nasal cavity with a tamponading balloon in the posterior nasopharynx.the evaluation of the nasopharyngeal soft tissues is somewhat limited by this tamponading balloon.there is fluid/mucosal thickening within the ethmoid, sphenoid and frontal air cells.there is mucosal thickening across the ostiomeatal complexes.there is no evidence of bone destruction.the nasal septum is midline.the lamina papyracea is intact bilaterally.the cribriform plates are equal in height.the anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.the sphenoid septum is midline.
summary: catheter with tamponading balloon entering the left nasal cavity and terminating within the posterior nasopharynx.air-fluid levels within bilateral maxillary sinuses.fluid/mucosal opacification within ethmoid, sphenoid and frontal air cells.

text: there are postoperative changes from prior left antrostomy, turbinectomy, and uncinectomy.there is mucosal thickening, and probably some fluid layering within the left maxillary sinus.there is also thickening and sclerosis of the walls of the left maxillary sinus.there is no significant mucosal thickening involving the right maxillary sinus, or frontal and sphenoid sinuses.there is minimal mucosal thickening involving the ethmoid sinuses.there is a right-sided ___ bullosa.the cribriform plates are symmetric.the lamina papyracea is intact, and the anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.visualized portions of the brain appear unremarkable.
summary: probable acute sinusitis, superimposed on chronic sinusitis of the left maxillary sinus, which shows postoperative changes.there is also minimal mucosal thickening involving the ethmoid sinuses.

text: in the frontal sinuses, no significant mucosal thickening is identified.in the maxillary sinuses, there is mild to moderate mucosal thickening in both sinuses in a predominantly circumferential distribution.some increased mucosal thickening in a lobular pattern is seen inferiorly.the omus are mildly narrowed by mucosal thickening on both sides.in the sphenoid sinus, there is mild mucosal thickening and frothy material on the right.an air fluid level and faint irregular curvilinear density is seen in the right posterior ethmoid air cell.minimal mucosal thickening is seen within the ethmoid sinus.there is a left nasal septal spur.the ethmoid roofs and cribriform plates are grossly parallel.there is no pneumatization of the anterior clinoid processes.evaluation of the orbits demonstrates banding in the left globe; several rounded, irregular foci of increased density are seen within the vitreous on both sides.
summary: mucosal thickening, predominantly in both maxillary sinuses and in the sphenoid sinus.given the history of immunodeficiency and decreased white cell count, sinusitis from an opoprtunistic infection cannot be excluded.banding prosthesis of left globe is consistent with the history of prior cmv chorioretinitis.several small densities within the vitreous of both globes is of uncertain significance; this should be correlated with any prior imaging studies if they are available from outside institution.these findings were discussed with dr.___ ___ on ___ at 2 p.m.

text: the frontal sinues are clear.there is extensive thickening of the left maxillary sinus with aerosilized secretions.there is mild thickening of the right maxillary sinus.there is minimal thickening of the central ethmoid cells.the sphenoid sinus shows minimal thickening.the right ostiomeatal unit is patent, the left shows soft tissue occlusion.the nasal septum deviates slightly to the left.the left cribriform plate is 3 mm higher than the right.the anterior clinoids are not pneumatized.the sphenoid septum inserts on the left carotid groove.
summary: extensive left maxillary sinus disease as described.minimal thickening elsewhere.

text: there is a large mucus retention cyst or polyp within the dependent portion of the left maxillary sinus.no fluid is seen within the paranasal sinuses.there is mild thickening of the ethmoid sinuses and possibly minimal thickening of the left-sided frontal sinuses as well.the infundibula for the right ostiomeatal complex is patent.there is mild mucosal thickening along the infundibulum on the left.the right anterior clinoid process is pneumatized.the nasal septum is midline.
summary: mucosal changes without evidence of acute sinusitis.

text: the bones are extensively demineralized.no displaced fractures are identified.there are no air-fluid levels within the paranasal sinuses.the previously described right sub-dural hematoma is partially visualized.
summary: no displaced fracture.

text: there are multiple facial fractures as previously described with interval reconstruction along the mandible, maxilla and right zygomatic arch.the right maxillary sinus appears no longer present.fractures through the orbit are again noted and there is infralateral subluxation of the globe on the right.fractures are seen to extend through the pterygoid plates and nasal septum.there is also avulsion of the tip of the mastoid process on the right with partial opacification of the remaining inferior air cells.though this is not a dedicated ct to evaluate the temporal bone, the course of the facial nerve canal can be followed and there is no fracture perceived to be interrupting its course.there are changes of stranding in the fat in the right parotid region with surgical drain noted at this site.there are no new fractures appreciated.there are a few prominent submandibular lymph nodes noted, more so on the left.the right temporomandibular joint remains dislocated.
summary: multiple fractures with interval reconstruction and continued subluxation of the right optic globe and dislocation of the right tmj.despite avulsion of the mastoid tip, there is no obvious interruption of the osseous facial nerve canal.if more detailed examination of the temporal bone is required, we will gladly repeat the study at your request with dedicated temporal bone images on the right.

text: a moderate amount of fluid is present in the right maxillary sinus.a small amount of fluid is present in the left maxillary sinus.a moderate amount of fluid is also present in the frontal and sphenoid sinuses.there is almost complete opacification of the ethmoid air cells.no fractures are present.the ostiomeatal units are not patent, due to the fluid and/or mucosal thickening.the cribriform plates are equal in height.the anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.the lamina papyracea is intact.
summary: no fractures present.moderately severe opacification of the sinuses.this may be inflammatory and/or post-traumatic in origin, and could relate to potential intubation of the patient.

text: there is very minimal polypoid thickening of the right frontal sinus.there is minimal thickening of the inferior aspect of the left maxillary sinus.the right maxillary sinus is clear.the ostiomeatal units are patent.the ethmoid and sphenoid sinuses are clear.the nasal septum deviates to the right with a small spur.the cribriform plates are symmetric in height.the anterior clinoids are not pneumatized.the sphenoid septum does not insert in either carotid groove.

text: the paranasal sinuses are normally aerated with no mucosal thickening or air fluid levels identified, other than a minimal degree of mucosal thickening just anterior to the left maxillary sinus ostium.the ostiomeatal units are patent.there is bilateral ___ bullosa, left greater than right.the lamina papyracea are intact.nasal septum is slightly deviated to the right.the osseous structures are unremarkable.

text: there are no fractures involving the facial bones.there is minimal mucosal thickening within the right maxillary sinus.there is a longitudinal fracture extending from the mandibular fossa of the temporal bone through the left mastoid air cells and across the temporomandibular joint space.there is blood within the middle ear space.there is normal joint alignment of the temporomandibular joints bilaterally.the fracture is nondisplaced.

text: fractures of the maxillary sinus walls have been repaired with plates and screws.there is normal anatomic alignment of the fractures.the maxillary sinuses are clear.there is no evidence of orbital floor abnormality.sphenoid, ethmoid and frontal sinuses are clear.the nasal cavity appears normal.the orbits are normal.there is slight irregularity of the nasal bones which may be the result of previous injury, but there is no longer malalignment evident that was present on the post traumatic ct.

text: no fractures are identified.the visualized paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are normally aerated.again noted is a midline frontal hematoma and a partially visualized right subdural hematoma.
summary: no fracture.

text: there is a hairline, nondisplaced fracture of the right zygomatic arch.there is also a slightly comminuted fracture of the squamous portion of the right temporal bone.no additional fractures are identified.the frontal sinuses are clear.there are numerous fluid levels within the ethmoid and sphenoid sinuses, not unexpected findings in this patient who is intubated.the maxillary sinuses are clear.the nasal septum has a rather tortuous configuration.although these images were not performed for evaluation of the brain parenchyma, again identified are multiple foci of hemorrhage in the left temporal lobe, both anteriorly and medially, the right frontal lobe, as well as layering within the large left frontal encephalomalacia cavity.the degree of intraparenchymal hemorrhage appears stable, as does the subarachnoid hemorrhage layering along the tentorium.no epidural hemorrhage is identified adjacent to the right temporal bone fracture.
summary: nondisplaced fracture of the right zygomatic arch.slightly comminuted fracture of the squamous portion of the right temporal bone.intra- and extraaxial hemorrhage as described previously.

text: there are minimal mucosal retention cysts or small polyps in the maxillary sinuses along the medial aspect of the left maxillary sinus and inferomedial aspect of the right maxillary sinus.the visualized paranasal sinuses are otherwise well pneumatized with no air-fluid levels.the ostiomeatal units are patent.there are conchae bullosae.the nasal septum is midline.there is pneumatization of the anterior clinoids.the laminae papyraceae are intact.

text: redemonstrated are innumerable fractures involving the nasal bones, maxillary sinuses, orbital walls, ethmoid air cells, left frontal sinus and frontal bone (depressed, as before), sphenoid sinuses, petrous apices, clivus, right posterior arch of c2, the basion and the zygomatic arches.these do not appear significantly changed in the interval.the degree of orbital emphysema has decreased.blood, gas, and possibly packing material fill the maxillary sinuses, nasal cavity, ethmoid air cells, and left frontal sinus.a small amount of pneumocephalus is present.a tiny depressed fracture of the interal wall of the left frontal sinus is noted, possibly slightly more depressed than on the prior study.fluid and secretions are present within the right frontal sinus.an et tube and orogastric tube are present.
summary: interval placement of ___ ___-___ type drain and a ventricular catheter.overall decrease in extend of orbital emphysema.otherwise, no change in the appearance of innumerable facial bones, skull, and cervical spine fractures.

text: fractures of the nasal bones, nasal septum, hard palate, right pterygoid plate, and maxilla bilaterally are noted.the right maxillary sinus is completely opacified with blood.the left is partially opacified.blood layers within the sphenoid sinuses bilaterally.there is a fracture through the right lateral wall of the orbit.there is emphysema the pre-septal region on left .hematoma is noted about the nose.the soft tissues are otherwise unremarkable.et tube and ng tube are in place.

text: the frontal, ethmoid, and sphenoid sinuses are normally aerated.bilateral maxillary mucus retention cysts are noted.the left anterior clinoid process is pneumatized.the ostiomeatal complexes are patent bilaterally.the skull base is only partly evaluated on this study and the known left skull base mass is smaller than on prior exams.

text: no fractures are identified.there is a mucus retention cyst within the right maxillary sinus, and some mucosal thickening along the medial left maxillary sinus wall.there is minor ethmoid air cell mucosal thickening as well.there is a leftward septal deviation.nasal bones are intact.

text: oropharyngeal and endotracheal tubes pass through the oropharynx.the previously noted metal fragment anterior to the c2 body is again noted.there is evidence of extensive intracranial hemorrhage status post placement of a ventriculostomy drain from the left.please refer to the head ct performed at the same time for findings regarding the brain parenchyma.pneumocephalus is again noted.a non-displaced fracture of the right pterygoid plates is again observed.however, the previously questioned basisphenoid fracture is not convincingly replicated on this study although prominent spheno-occipital synchondrosis is likely see.there is a non-displaced fracture of the right frontal bone extending to the lateral wall of the right orbit.the paranasal sinuses remain partially opacified with air fluid levels seen in the maxillary sinuses.
summary: fracture of the right zygomatic process extending to the right lateral orbital wall.questionable fracture of the basisphenoid not convincing replicated on this study.previously seen fracture of the right pterygoid plates.continued opacification of the paranasal sinuses.please refer to the head ct for findings regarding the brain abnormalities noted previously.

text: there is almost complete opacification of the maxillary, frontal, ethmoid, sphenoid sinuses.the ostiomeatal units are not patent.the cribriform plates are equal in height.the anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.the laminal papyracea is intact.the sphenoid sinus septum is mid-line.

text: polypoid mucosal thickening is present at the right maxillary sinus.both ostiomeatal complexes are widely patent.there is a right nasal septal spur with associated polypoid mucosal thickening, likely benign, but direct visualization would help to confirm this supposition.the left maxillary sinus, both frontal, ethmoid, and sphenoid sinuses are clear.

text: there are no fractures.the paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are normally aerated.there is stranding in the superficial fat overlying the left maxilla, below the zygomatic arch.the patient is intubated.
summary: no fractures.

text: there is new opacification of the dependent posterior portion of the left sphenoid sinus, which appears more consistent with mucosal thickening than with an air-fluid level.otherwise, there are no air-fluid levels in the paranasal sinuses.the visualized osseous structures appear unremarkable.

text: there is an anterior to posterior linear fracture through the right side of the hard palate and maxillary ridge.there are fractures of the posterior wall of the right maxillary sinus, and right pterygoid plates.the lateral orbital walls are somewhat irregular, but a clearly defined fracture is not seen on this study.please refer to the previous examination from ___.there are nasal bone fractures.there is a nasal septal fracture.there is fluid in the paranasal sinuses and some of this is dense, consistent with blood.the overall appearance is not significantly changed since the previous day.
summary: facial fractures, as described.overall stability, compared to the previous examination.

text: there is near complete opacification of the right mastoid air cells with fluid and/or debris noted in the right middle ear.additionally, there is partial opacification of the left mastoid air cells.debris is also noted within the left middle ear, although this appears to be more solid.there is a small amount of fluid layering within the sphenoid sinus.mild mucosal thickening is noted within the left maxillary sinus.there is minimal mucosal thickening within the ethmoid sinuses.the frontal sinuses appear normal.coronally reformatted images redemonstrate the above findings.et tube and ng tube are present.
summary: findings are concerning for mastoiditis.additionally, a small amount of fluid layering within the sphenoid sinus could be related to intubation, but sinusitis should be considered as well.

text: there is no mucosal thickening throughout any of the paranasal sinuses.there is a trace amount of fluid in the sphenoid sinus on the left of doubtful clinical significance.the soft tissues are unremarkable.the bones are within normal limits.the appearance of the orbits is also unremarkable.the imaged portions of brain are within normal limits for technique.

text: fracture of the right temporal bone is partially imaged on this study.there are adjacent tiny bubbles of air seen within the soft tissues next to the fracture site.there is mucosal thickening involving both frontal, ethmoid, maxillary, and sphenoid sinuses.there is opacification of the right mastoid air cells with a transverse fracture of the right temporal bone identified.no other definite fractures are seen.an endotracheal tube and nasogastric tube are seen entering the oropharynx.there is blow out fracture of the right orbital floor with herniation of orbital fat.the inferior rectus muscle is normal in position.
summary: partial visualization of fracture within the right temporal bone with adjacent soft tissue air present.partially imaged obligue/longitudinal fracture through the right temporal bone with opacification of the right mastoid air cells.mucosal thickening involving all the paranasal sinuses.no other definite fractures are present.air in infratemporal fossa.blow out fracture right orbital floor and subtle right orbital emphysema.

text: there is a fracture through the inferior left orbital rim and orbital floor.there is no displacement of the inferior rectus muscle though there is a small amount of inferiorly displaced orbital fat.fracture fragments are present along the course fo the orbital floor, but do not impinge on orbital structures.there is also a comminuted fracture of the left zygoma, extending through the zygomatic arch as well as a comminuted fracture of the left lateral maxillary sinus wall, and a slightly displaced fracture of the left lateral orbit.the left zygoma is depressed and medially displaced.there are some fragments of the maxillary sinus which extend into the inferior sinus cavity and there is also a large free fragment of bone in the superior aspect of the sinus.the left lamina papyracea is intact.the floor of the anterior cranial fossa and frontal sinus are intact.there are no fractures of the anterior clinoids appreciated.the nasal bones are intact.there is minimal increased density along the lateral wall of the orbit, but no frank intraorbital hematoma is identified.the optic nerve appears grossly normal.there is left preseptal soft tissue swelling.
summary: multiple displaced fragments of the comminuted left zygoma and maxillary sinus fracture as well as a left orbital floor fracture.there is no impingement on intraorbital structures at this time.

text: patient is status post open reduction internal fixation with microfixation plates and fixation screws along the bilateral zygomatic, maxillary, and nasal bone fractures.the mesh material in the right inferior orbit is stable without significant interval changes since ___, examination.the right globe and retro-orbital structures, especially the extraocular muscles are intact.there is near-anatomic alignment of the reduced fractures.numerous other facial and skull fractures seen as previously described.mucosal thickening present in the right frontal and both ethmoid air cells.total opacification of the sphenoid sinus by soft tissue or fluid density is also seen.there is an osseous fracture fragment superior to the left cribriform plate which projects into the left inferior- frontal brain parenchyma with associated edema.this is an area of potential concern for future csf leak and meningitis.findings were discussed with dr.___ of the trauma service on ___ in am.(please note delay in reporting relates to post-processing of images for post-surgical planning purposes.
summary: near-anatomic alignment with multiple facial fractures with microfixation plates and compression screws.there is placement of mesh material in the right inferior orbit.no significant interval change since ___, examination.left cribriform plate fracture with an osseous fragment which projects into the left inferior frontal lobe.this finding was noted on ___ as well and also discussed with house-staff at that time.this raises concern for an area of potential future cerebrospinal fluid leak and/or meningitis.study findings discussed in detail with dr.___.

text: the patient is intubated.there is an ng tube, which coils in the posterior nasopharynx.the inferior-most portion of this tube is not imaged.there is a fluid level within the left maxillary antrum and sphenoid sinus.there is partial opacification of the ethmoid air cells.there is subtotal opacification of a hypoplastic left frontal air cell.there is circumferential thickening within both sphenoid air cells with subtotal opacification.additionally, there is thickening within the right maxillary antrum.there is complete opacification of the right mastoid air cells with opacification of the right middle ear cavity.there is subtotal opacification of the left mastoid air cells, there is fluid in the left epitympanic cavity.there is increased soft tissue attenuation within the nasopharynx relating to the patient's intubated status.images of the intracranial contents show prominence of the ventricles.no suspicious lesions are seen within the bones.
summary: fluid level within the right maxillary sinus.subtotal opacification of the paranasal sinuses with complete opacification of the right mastoid air cells and right middle ear cavity.such sinus opacification is frequently seen in patients who are intubated.fluid levels in the maxillary sinus and complete opacification of the right middle ear and mastoids, however, do raise the suspicion for acute sinus infection.this finding was discussed with dr.___ ___ on ___, at 19:00.

text: there is a slightly unusual appearance to the articulation of the clivus with the right temporal bone, but no fracture is appreciated.there are no paranasal sinus fluid levels.the ear canals are patent.the mastoids are well aerated.the tmj's are intact.the globes are normal.the imaged portions of the brain parenchyma are unremarkable.note is made that the patient is missing his bottom two front teeth, said by report to be lost during trauma.an et tube and ng tube are noted.
summary: fracture invovling the anterior mandible along the roots of the lower incisors and with slight anterior dispacement of the fragments (arrows).soft tissue swelling of the nose noted, a subtle fracture cannot be excluded.revised findings discussed with dr ___ at 12.15 pm on ___.

text: numerous plates and screws across the numerous facial fractures are again noted, as previously described.angular medial bowing of the medial wall of the orbit persists.some of the osseous fragments formerly comprising the lateral wall of the orbit are no longer apparent.the roof of the left orbit has less angular deformity, but small defects persist.a large defect is again noted in the floor of the left orbit.the resultant expansion of the volume of the entire left orbit likely accounts for the observed enophthalmos of the left globe.a midline defect in the frontal skull is more apparent below the various plates and screws at the level of the frontal sinus.the ethmoid air cells are better aerated.opacities in the sphenoid sinus have mostly resolved.the left maxillary sinus remains mostly opacified, but the right maxillary sinus is relatively well aerated.the mastoid air cells are clear.numerous other fractures are again noted, including the slight irregularity to the right lamina papyracea, small gaps in the lateral wall of the right orbit, multiple nasal bone fractures, fractures of the pterygoid plates bilaterally, and healing deformities of the mandible.3d reconstructions support the above-noted osseous findings.residual low attenuation regions in both frontal lobes from prior contusions are markedly decreased since the prior study.

text: again seen are numerous fractures involving the superior, medial, inferior, and lateral orbital walls as well as the lateral wall of the maxillary sinus.the conformation of the orbital fractures is not significantly changed with the continued medial displacement of the medial wall fractures and inferior displacement of the inferior wall fractures.osseous fragments are again noted along the superior margin of the orbit.abnormalities of the left globe are again noted.the globe is diminutive in size and predominantly high in attenuation.enophthalmos is also noted with apparent laxity of the rectus muscles.moderate mucosal thickening is noted in the left maxillary sinus.mild mucosal thickening is also noted in the right maxillary, ethmoid, and left frontal sinuses.

text: there is mild mucosal thickening of the anterior ethmoid, frontal and sphenoid sinuses.the maxillary sinuses are well aerated.there are moderate bilateral haller cells which slightly narrow the ostiomeatal complexes without causing occlusion.there is discontinuity of the left orbital floor, likely reflecting an old orbital floor fracture.please correlate clinically.the cribriform plates are equal in height.the anterior clinoids are not pneumatized.the sphenoid septum inserts on the left carotid groove.no focal lytic or sclerotic bony lesions are identified.visualized portions of the brain parenchyma appear unremarkable.

text: there is pronounced soft tissue swelling over the right orbit, and to a lesser extent over the left orbit.there is bilateral orbital emphysema, including air in the postseptal spaces bilaterally.the globes appear grossly intact, although there is some proptosis of the right side relative to the left, as well as mild inferior medial shift of the right globe.this is likely related to a small hematoma in the superolateral orbit, adjacent to the orbital roof fracture site.the maxillary and sphenoid sinuses show air-fluid levels consistent with hemorrhage.there is also soft tissue density, presumably hemorrhage in the nasal and oropharynx.the mastoid air cells are clear.there are multiple fractures involving the facial bones.there are bilateral nondisplaced frontal bone fractures.also, the orbital grooves and medial orbital walls have multiple minimally displaced fractures bilaterally.the orbital roof fractures are displaced upwards by 1-2 mm as best seen on the coronal images.these fractures also involve the cribriform plates, without significant displacement, and the lateral orbital walls as well.in addition, there are multiple minimally displaced fractures in the ethmoid cells and of the nasal bones.bilaterally, the maxillary bones show fractures along the anteromedial aspects of the maxillary sinuses, with a few mm of posterior displacement and impaction.there is no fracture evident involving either carotid canal.
summary: opacification of the paranasal sinuses with air-fluid levels, consistent with hemorrhage.the presence of an air-fluid level in the sphenoid sinus can be suggestive of an occult skull base fracture as well although none is seen on this study.bilateral orbital emphysema and soft tissue swelling about the orbits, although the globes appear intact.the postseptal fat appears intact as well.adjacent to the fracture of the right orbital roof, there is a small hematoma , lying outside the extraocular muscles, with mild downward displacement of the globe on the right side.complex facial bone fractures, with posterior displacement to a small extent of the nasal and anterior aspects of the maxillary bones.fractures of the orbital rooves and medial orbital walls, as well as the cribriform plates and frontal bones.

text: for the description of the intracranial findings, please refer to the separate report of head ct (clip ___).as on that examination, there is moderate mucosal thickening involving all paranasal sinuses, with probable small mucous retention cyst in the floor of the left maxillary antrum, connoting chronic inflammatory disease.this may explain the left maxillary fluid level, with no significant high density material to specifically suggest acute hemorrhage.the sinus, particularly left maxillary, walls are intact, with no acute fracture.the nasal bones, jaws and teeth also appear intact.the middle ear cavities and largely included mastoid air cells are clear.

text: comparison is made to head cts dated ___ and ___.no orbital fractures are seen.again seen are left skull fractures with extension into the floor of the left anterior cranial fossa.nasal fractures are also again noted.right craniotomy is present.small pocket of gas is seen intracranially and there are small hyperdensities of the frontal lobes bilaterally, which likely represent hematomas.again seen is fluid collection anteriorly on the right consistent with a partial resection of the right frontal lobe.there is still residual mild right to left shift of the normally midline structures.there is dense opacification of the frontal and ethmoid sinuses.air-fluid levels are seen within the sphenoid and maxillary sinuses bilaterally.these findings may be due to recent extubation.fluid is seen within the middle ear cavities bilaterally.there are few punctate metallic densities seen within the soft tissues over the mandible on the right.
summary: multiple fractures of the left side of the skull with extension to the floor of the anterior cranial fossa.residual bilateral frontal hemorrhagic contusions and right to left shift of the normally midline structures.post-surgical changes of the right frontal lobe.

text: again seen is a left medial orbital wall fracture with medial displacement and a small amount of soft tissue density extending into the ethmoid sinuses.there is no evidence of entrapment.surrounding the globe on the left is an area of soft tissue density which either represents inflammatory change or hematoma.this soft tissue density extends retro- orbitally and measures approximately 5 mm in ap direction.it appears that some of this fluid is accounting for proptosis.no additional fractures are visualized.again seen within the right sphenoid sinuses, bony thickening and opacification with no evidence of inward or outward mass effect or lytic changes.these findings appear to be consistent more so with chronic sinusitis rather than a malignant process.
summary: left medial orbital wall blow-out fracture with no evidence of extraocular muscle entrapment.there is retrobulbar soft tissue density extending anteriorly surrounding the globes which may represent hematoma.

text: there are bilateral orbital roof fractures with intraorbital air present.there are several small fragments that project into the csf space overlying the left orbital roof.there is a segmental fracture of the right lateral orbital wall with 5 mm of internal depression of the superior fragment, and suggestion of impalement of the right lateral rectus muscle.there is a right inferior orbital wall fracture with inferior segmental displacement of the inferior orbital wall.though there is an extensively comminuted fracture of the sphenoid ___, at the orbital apex, the optic strut appears intact and the optic canal is not compromised.there is a right medial orbital wall fracture with no entrapment of the medial rectus muscle.there are fractures of the anterior wall of the right maxillary sinus with posterior extension through the hard palate.there are multiple fractures of the posterior and lateral walls of the right maxillary sinus, as well.there also appears to be a nondisplaced fracture of the lateral wall of the left maxillary sinus.there are multiple displaced nasal fractures.a coronally- oriented fracture component, which may represent further extension of the right palatal fracture, involves the base of the left pterygoid process, extending into those pterygoid plates; there is no evidence of mid-facial separation, however.note is also made of a right mandibular fracture.numerous foci of air are present in the soft tissues of the face, likely secondary to the numerous fractures that are present.there is pneumocephalus underlying a right skull fracture located anterior to the mastoid air cells.the images also incompletely demonstrate a transverse fracture of the left temporal bone, extending through the glenoid fossa extending toward the carotid canal in the petrous temporal bone (better depicted on brain ct study).
summary: numerous facial fractures, as described above.

text: the patient is intubated.there is virtual complete opacification, with some bony remodeling, of the bilateral ethmoid sinuses, with extensive mucosal thickening and fluid levels involving the bilateral frontal, maxillary and sphenoid sinuses, but no definite acute hemorrhage, like representing acute- on- chronic inflammatory change .the nasal septum is moderately deviated to the right with a small osseous spur; however, there is a slightly displaced, comminuted fracture of the more superior portion of the bony septum, with fluid (or blood) filling the nasal cavity.the vomer appears intact, and no other facial fracture is seen.the mastoid air cells and middle ear cavities are clear.
summary: acute comminuted fracture of the upper bony nasal septum, with deviation to the right, and small osseous spur.no other facial bone fracture.acute-on-chronic pansinus inflammatory disease.

text: mild mucosal thickening is seen within the left maxillary sinus.there is minimal mucosal thickening within several ethmoid air spaces.otherwise, paranasal sinuses appear normally aerated.ostiomeatal units are patent.nasal septum is midline.lamina papyracea are intact.
summary: mild mucosal thickening within the left maxillary sinus.minimal mucosal thickening within several ethmoid air spaces.no evidence of osseous destruction or air-fluid levels.

text: there is no evidence of mucosal thickening or air-fluid levels within the maxillary, ethmoid, sphenoid, or frontal sinuses.no evidence of bony involvement of the visualized facial bones.surrounding soft tissues are grossly unremarkable on this non-contrast-enhanced study.

text: the findings are completely unchanged from the head ct of one day previous.there is partial aeration of the maxillary sinuses bilaterally, with a moderate-to-severe amount of soft tissue opacity within them, right greater than left.maxillary sinuses are nearly completely opacified posteriorly.there is moderate mucosal thickening associated with the ethmoid air cells and within the sphenoid sinus.the frontal sinuses are relatively well aerated.the ostiomeatal complexes are opacified.
summary: severe soft tissue opacity and mucosal thickening within the paranasal sinuses as described.in this neutropenic patient, opportunistic infections are to be considered.

text: there is near complete opacification of the left maxillary sinus with interspersed foci of air.a small amount of fluid or mucosal thickening is noted in the right sphenoid sinus.the orbits are unremarkable.osseous and soft tissue structures are unremarkable.there is malalignement of left nasal bone possibly due to previous trauma.
summary: left maxillary sinusitis.

text: mild mucosal thickening is seen within the ethmoid sinuses.there is a small left maxillary polypoid soft tissue density.an osteoma is noted in the left frontal sinus.otherwise, no air-fluid levels or evidence of bone destruction are seen.ostiomeatal units appear patent.
summary: mild mucosal thickening as described above.no evidence of air- fluid levels or bone destruction.

text: there is a slightly depressed fracture of the anterior wall of the left maxillary sinus.subcutaneous air and soft tissue swelling overlying this fracture is seen.layering hemorrhage is seen within the left maxillary sinus.there also appears to be a small nondisplaced inferior left orbital fracture.no other definite fractures are seen.note that the ng tube is coiled within the mouth and oral/hypopharynx.

text: the frontal, ethmoid, sphenoid, and maxillary sinuses are clear.there are haller cells bilaterally.there is a small right nasal septal spur.the optic struts are pneumatized.
summary: no evidence of acute or chronic sinusitis.if axial imaging of the paranasal sinuses is desired, the patient can be rescanned at no additional charge.

text: the patient is status post multiple comminuted fractures of the frontal bones, one of the fracture line going through right frontal sinus.the fracture lines are narrower and less conspicuous compared to the prior study, representing healing.the patient is status post fixation of some of these fractures.no new fracture or no new displacement is noted.paranasal sinuses and nasopharynx are clear.soft tissue is unremarkable.the evaluation of the brain parenchyma is extremely limited due to algorithm.

text: the frontal, sphenoid, right ethmoid air cells, and maxillary sinuses are well pneumatized and aerated without evidence of air-fluid levels or mucosal thickening.there is minimal circumferential mucosal thickening involving a single left anterior ethmoidal air cell.remaining left ethmoid air cells are well pneumatized and aerated.the ostiomeatal unit bilaterally are widely patent.the mastoid air cells bilaterally are well aerated.no air-fluid levels are demonstrated.the nasal septum is deviated towards the right, and there is a moderate-sized right nasal spur.the anterior clinoid processes bilaterally are aerated.the cribriform plates are symmetric in height.the lamina papyracea is intact.the sphenoid sinus septum is multipartite with the mean insertion upon the midline.
summary: minimal mucosal thickening involving the left anterior ethmoid air cell.no other signs of sinus disease.

text: the patient is intubated, with orogastric tube in place.a minimally displaced fracture is seen involving the lateral/inferior wall of the posterior orbit, through the sphenoid bone.on the sagittally reformatted images, a nondisplaced fracture along the posterior/superior wall of the right orbital apex is also noted.within the limits of this examination, the lamina papyracea appears intact, as does the orbital floors.multiple foci of extraconal air are seen at the superior aspect of the right orbit, with associated tissue or fluid density suggesting blood.this is contiguous with the soft tissue swelling seen superior and lateral to the right orbit.mucosal thickening is seen within the frontal ethmoid recess, in the ethmoid air cells, with air-fluid levels seen in the sphenoid sinuses as well as the right maxillary antrum.mucosal thickening is also seen at the left maxillary antrum.in addition, aerosolized secretions/fluid is seen within the nasal and oropharyngeal cavities.
summary: minimally displaced right sphenoid fracture, at the inferior/lateral wall of the right orbital apex.nondisplaced fracture of the posterior/superior wall of the right orbital apex (series 104b, image 48; series 2, image 33).air-fluid levels seen within the sphenoid sinus and right maxillary antrum, without definite associated fractures of the orbital floor or wall of the maxillary sinus.small amount of extraconal fluid and air is seen along the superior right orbit, possibly contiguous with the soft tissue swelling/hematoma just superior to the right orbit.wet read was posted to the ed dashboard at the time of interpretation.

text: frontal sinuses are clear.there is scattered opacification of ethmoid air cells.mild mucosal thickening of both maxillary sinuses is noted, with aerosolized secretions; some high density material is seen within the mucosal thickening likely representing inspissated secretions vs fungal colonization.sphenoid sinuses are clear.mastoid air cells are clear.small amount of debris in both external auditory canals is noted, likely cerumen.cavernous carotids are calcified.superior portion of nasal cavity is patent.sphenoethmoid recesses are patent.there is a destructive expansile lesion of the right mandibular coronoid process, not completely imaged, but without discernable soft tissue lesion.periosteal new bone formation is also seen.left mandibular ramus and remainder of mandible are normal.8 mm soft tissue nodule seen along the lateral aspect of the left masseter.this may represent a lymph node or a salivary gland tumor.left temporomandibular joint is within normal limits.right shows degenerative change.
summary: destructive lesion of right mandibular ramus, likely metastasis.mild sinusitis as described above; high density material may represent inspissated secretions vs fungal colonization.8mm left subcutaneous nodule near masseter - may represent lymph node.dedicated neck ct should be obtained for further evaluation.

text: there is an air-fluid level with aerosolized secretions in the left sphenoid sinus.aerosolized secretions are also identified within the right sphenoid sinus.the ostiomeatal complexes are patent bilaterally.the nasal septum is midline with minimal rightward deviation.there are old nasal bone fractures.the olfactory fossa is ___ type i bilaterally.there is pneumatization of the left optic strut as well as pneumatization of the base of the right optic strut.there are no osseous erosions.

text: there are lateral subluxations of the mandible at both temporomandibular joints with sclerosis at the temporomandibular joints.this appearance is likely chronic.there is no evidence of a fracture or dislocation.there is mild mucosal thickening in the frontal and bilateral maxillary sinuses, and among the ethmoid cells, without air-fluid levels.there is soft tissue swelling above the right orbit.the intraorbital contents are unremarkable.
summary: mild bilateral temporomandibular subluxations, with both mandibular heads positioned somewhat laterally.the abnormality is likely chronic.mild mucosal thickening in the paranasal sinuses.no evidence of fracture.

text: there is a medial blowout fracture of the lamina papyracea of the left orbit along the posterior medial wall.there is an inferior blowout fracture with inferiorly displaced orbital floor, also most prominent posteriorly.there is protrusion of fat through the inferior orbital wall defect, but no muscular herniation.there is associated opacification of the ethmoid and maxillary sinuses that represent a mixture of mucus and hemorrhage.there are bilateral nasal bone fractures along the nasal bridge.there are bilateral unerupted maxillary and mandibular molars.mastoid air cells are clear.there is mild mucosal thickening of the sphenoid sinuses.

text: the ostiomeatal complexes are both patent.there is mild mucosal thickening adjacent to the os of the right ostiomeatal complex.however, there are no air-fluid levels present to indicate the presence of acute sinusitis.there is minimal mucosal thickening at the floor of the left maxillary sinus.the remainder of the paranasal sinuses are well pneumatized.there are bilateral ___ bullosa present.the olfactory fossa is ___ type i on the right and ___ type ii on the left.the nasal septum is midline.the optic struts are not pneumatized.it is an incidental finding that there has been a left lens replacement.
summary: no evidence of acute or chronic sinusitis.there is mild mucosal thickening adjacent to the os of the right ostiomeatal complex.

text: fluid is noted filling approximately ___ of the left maxillary sinus.the other visualized sinuses are unremarkable.multiple non-displaced distal nasal bone fractures are identified.left orbital floor fracture noted yet non-displaced and therefore without herniation of orbital contents.small non- displaced fractures of the left zygomatic arch, posterior wall of the maxillary sinus and the lateral wall of the left orbit are also noted.bilateral subchondral cyst formation of the temporomandibular joint with joint space narrowing present.
summary: multiple nondisplaced fractures of the facial bones are identified on the left including the zygomatic arch, orbital floor, posterior wall of the maxillary sinus and the lateral wall of the orbit.fluid within the left maxillary sinus likely represents hematoma.bilateral degenerative joint disease of the temporomandibular joint.

text: there are minimally displaced, comminuted nasal bone fractures, bilaterally, with mild leftward deformity of the anterior nasal bones and swelling of the overlying soft tissues.there is a ___ bullosa limited to the vertical portion of the right middle turbinate, associated with s- shaped deviation, posteriorly.there is only minimal mucosal thickening involving the maxillary antra, including the region of the ostiomeatal units, which are partially obstructed; the ethmoidal air cells, sphenoid and frontal sinuses are clear.the orbits are unremarkable.very limited views of the brain are unremarkable.

text: there is mucosal thickening noted in the maxillary sinuses bilaterally, right great than left, there is almost complete opacification of ethmoid sinus.there is mucosal thickening in the sphenoid and frontal sinuses as well.there are no fluid levels.ostiomeatal units are obstructed by mucosal thickening.the cribriform plates are equal in height.the anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.the lamina preparation is intact.the nasoseptum is midline.there is a right preseptal preorbital soft tissue edema and medial postseptal extraconal fat stranding.intraconal fat and globe are normal.there are no abscesses.
summary: mucosal thickening of the paranasal sinuses as described above.preseptal periorbital soft tissue edema and postseptal extraconal fat stranding, most consistent with a cellulitis.findings were discussed with dr.___ at 4 pm ___.

text: the patient is status post repair of the lateral wall of the right orbit, anterior walls of both maxillary sinuses, and bilateral inferior orbital rims.there are multiple persistent facial fractures including the left orbit lateral wall, roofs of both orbits, and bilateral cribriform plates.there is also a persistent depressed skull fracture of the left calvarium, which is stable.there appears to be slightly less encroachment of the right optic nerve.there is persistent subcutaneous emphysema anteriorly as well as high attenuation fluid, likely hemorrhage in the maxillary sinuses, sphenoid sinuses, and ethmoid air cells.again seen is a left subdural hematoma.
summary: status post repair of several facial bone fractures, with persistent fractures in both orbital ribs, cribriform plates, and left orbit and calvarium.close clinical followup is warranted to evaluate for bilateral optic nerve damage.persistent left subdural hematoma.

text: diffuse opacification of the frontal sinuses, ethmoid sinuses, and maxillary sinuses appears unchanged.there is perhaps more opacification of the sphenoid sinus air cells bilaterally.there is increased air within the left nasolacrimal duct as well as contiguous subcutaneous emphysema medial to the left globe in a preseptal locale.additionally, posterior to this gas, a small pocket of gas is noted abutting the left lamina papyracea and lateral to the medial rectus muscle.while no definable discontinuity of the left lamina papyracea is identified, the presence of this air raises the question of a non- visualized breach of this structure, vs.spread of infection by emissary veins.remainder of the visualized osseous structures and mastoid air cells appear unremarkable.orbits appear normal, with preservation of intraorbital fat planes.
summary: persistent opacification of multiple paranasal sinuses with worsening of opacity within the sphenoid sinus.although no definite bony erosion is identified, increased subcutaneous air as well as air adjacent to the lamina papyracea on the left raises the question of breach of this structure, as well as transmission of infection via emissary veins, the latter mechanism being invoked to account for the tiny amount of left extraconal gas adjacent to the left lamina papyracea.these findings were discussed with dr.___ ___ at approximately 4:30 p.m.on ___.

text: the nondisplaced fracture involving the posteromedial left orbital wall is again identified.the fracture of the left temporal bone is better evaluated on the prior ct.no new fractures are identified.the orbital contents appear unremarkable.the visualized paranasal sinuses demonstrate mucosal thickening of the sphenoid air cells.the maxillary sinuses, ethmoid and frontal air cells are clear.opacification of multiple left mastoid air cells is again seen.

text: there is stable appearance of nondisplaced fracture involving the medial and posterior left orbital wall.fracture of the left temporal bone is better seen on accompanying head ct.no new fractures are identified.orbital contents are unremarkable.air-fluid level is again seen in the right sphenoid sinus with mild mucosal thickening involving the left sphenoid and right maxillary sinuses.a minor amount of mucosal thickening is also identified in some of the left-sided ethmoid air cells.opacification of multiple mastoid air cells is again identified.

text: there is a hairline fracture in the lateral aspect of the right orbital roof.there is subcutaneous soft tissue swelling overlying the zygomaticofrontal suture.the right orbital contents, as well as the left orbit, visualized pharyngeal/parapharyngeal/retropharyngeal soft tissues, floor of the mouth, and bilateral submandibular and parotid glands are within normal limits.there is a mucus retention cyst within the right maxillary sinus.the rest of the paranasal sinuses, middle ear cavities, and mastoid air cells are clear bilaterally.

text: there is air-fluid level in the right side of the sphenoid sinus.the left side of the sphenoid sinus is completely opacified.there is minimal mucosal thickening in the ethmoid sinus.maxillary sinuses and nasopharynx, the visualized portion of mastoid air cells are clear.there is no evidence of bone erosion.bilateral osteomeatal complexes are patent.cribriform plates are intact.anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.

text: no new acute fracture is identified.as seen on the cervical spine ct, evidence of prior trauma is present with bilateral mandibular condylar fractures.there also appear to be old healed fractures of the mandibular angles, bilaterally.evidence of prior surgical intervention is seen in this area with wires present.surgical cerclage wires are also seen in the posterior maxilla bordering the posterior walls of the maxillary sinuses.there is an old fracture, minimally displaced, of the maxillary alveolus.fluid is seen in the left maxillary sinus and the sphenoid sinus.fluid is also seen in the right mastoid air cells and external auditory canal.no temporal bone fracture is identified, and the ossicles appear intact.there is mild mucosal thickening seen in the ethmoid, right maxillary, and anterior sphenoid sinuses.the intraorbital contents and laminae papyracea are intact.
summary: evidence of prior trauma and surgical intervention, as described above.no acute fracture identified.findings were discussed discussed with dr.___ ___ at the completion of the exam.

text: there is orthopedic hardware in place transfixing bilateral nasal bone fractures inferiorly as well as fractures of bilateral anterior walls of the maxillary sinuses.there is now anatomic alignment at the nasomaxillary junction bilaterally.other multiple bony fractures are without significant change and include bilateral superior/anterior nasal bone comminuted fractures, persistent bony fragments and minimally displaced fractures of the anterior walls of the maxillary sinuses, minimally displaced fractures of the posterolateral walls of both maxillary sinuses, and bilateral slightly displaced medial and lateral pterygoid plate fractures.there remains complete opacification of both maxillary sinuses.there is now greater opacification with superimposed air/fluid levels in both sphenoid sinuses, bilateral ethmoid air cells, and bilateral sphenoid sinuses, which may be at least partially related to the recent surgery.there is extensive soft tissue swelling and subcutaneous multiple air bubbles within the anterior portion of the face, most likely related to the recent surgery.the visualized brain, orbital contents, and the parapharyngeal soft tissues are within normal limits.there are multiple up to 1.3 cm in size bilateral submandibular, jugular digastric, and level v lymph nodes, as before.
summary: new orthopedic hardware within the nasal bones and both maxilla with good approximation of the fracture fragments.stable appearance of several other fractures and bony fragments not transfixed by orthopedic hardware, as discussed above.soft tissue changes in the anterior portion of the face and paranasal sinuses, most of which are likely related to recent surgery.multiple bilateral top normal in size, level ii and level v lymph nodes.

text: there are patent nasal-antral ostia, bilaterally.uncinate processes are intact, however, and there are no signs of post-surgical change.the appearance is smooth and symmetric, suggesting that the appearance may be congenital, or perhaps, related to remote inflammation.there is minimal mucosal thickening in the ethmoid sinuses, with slight circumferential mucosal thickening in the sphenoid sinus.the maxillary and frontal sinuses are clear.there are no air-fluid levels to suggest acute sinusitis.there is a large bony spur associated with mild leftward deviation of the nasal septum, but the middle meatus is widely patent.the orbits and surrounding soft tissue structures are unremarkable.the osseous structures are within normal limits.

text: diffuse soft tissue gas is noted within the soft tissues of the face bilaterally.the nasal bones demonstrate multiple comminuted impacted telescoping fractures anteriorly.horizontal fracture transects the nasal septum midline.comminuted fractures are noted through the inferolateral, superior, and medial walls of the maxillary sinus bilaterally indicative of bilateral lefort ii fractures.a nondisplaced vertically oriented fracture is noted through the hard palate on the right.hematoma fully opacifies the maxillary sinuses bilaterally.
summary: bilateral lefort ii fractures.telescoping impacted anterior nasal bone fracture.hematomas opacify the maxillary sinuses bilaterally.horizontally oriented fracture through the medial portion of the nasal septum with mild leftward displacement of the fracture fragment.vertically oriented nondisplaced fracture of the right hard palate.please see dedicated c- spine for multiple cervical spinal fractures.

text: the patient is intubated and there is a nasogastric tube coursing into the esophagus.there are air-fluid levels in the sphenoid and the bilateral maxillary sinuses, and opacification of the ethmoid cells and nasal cavity.this appearance has progressed over two days and may relate to intubation.only a portion of the known nondisplaced left parietal fracture is visualized.no other fracture is identified.there is fluid in the left middle ear and mastoid air cells, which can suggest underlying injury but no fracture line is identified and this appearance is new since the first head ct from ___.there is a lucency associated with the first lower right premolar tooth which may relate to a tooth abscess.clinical correlation is recommended.multiple foci of intracranial hemorrhage are described on the accompanying report of a head ct from the same day.
summary: other than the known parietal fracture, no definite fracture identified.lucency about the lower right first premolar, possibly a tooth abscess.correlation with clinical examination is recommended.

text: evaluation of the intracranial parenchyma again demonstrates the patient's known intraventricular and intraparenchymal hemorrhage.there is secondary hydrocephalus.dense calcification of the internal carotid arteries is visualized.the frontal and sphenoid sinuses are clear.the left maxillary sinus is also clear.there is minimal opacification of some of the ethmoidal air cells.stable peripheral thickening of the right maxillary sinus is again seen with aerosolized secretions.this has not changed from the prior examination 2 days prior.the osteomeatal complex on the right is opacified.the left osteomeatal complex is patent.there is a large rightward nasal spur impinging upon the right inferior turbinate.mild rightward nasal septal deviation is also present.there are large bilateral ___ bullosa present.evaluation of the osseous structures demonstrates no evidence for fracture.the orbits are unremarkable.there is atherosclerosis of the carotids.

text: the study is significantly limited by patient motion artifact, which most significantly affected the region of interest, specifically the sphenoid sinus.previously seen hyperdense air/fluid level in the right maxillary sinus has resolved.a small mucous retention cyst in the posterior aspect of the right maxillary sinus remains.the right sphenoid sinus air cell remains virtually completely opacified, while the left sphenoid sinus air cell has undergone partial clearing.a few small mucous retention cysts are seen in the left maxillary sinus.the ethmoid air cells and the frontal sinuses bilaterally are grossly within normal limits.there is partial opacification of mastoid air cells bilaterally, and small amount of fluid in the left middle ear cavity.the patient remains intubated.the visualized brain shows no evidence of acute intracranial hemorrhage.
summary: study significantly degraded by patient motion artifact, demonstrating resolution of the hyperdense air/fluid level in the right maxillary sinus, partial clearing of the left sphenoid sinus air cell, and relatively stable, virtually complete opacification of the right sphenoid sinus.ent consultation suggested, and particularly if drainage is contemplated, a repeat study is advised.results discussed with dr.___ ___ on ___ at 3:00 p.m.

text: there is an ng tube travelling through the right nasal passage.the paranasal sinuses are well aerated.there is no evidence of mucosal thickening or sinus fluid.there is a right ___ bullosa.the ostiomeatal units are patent bilaterally.no fractures are identified.the orbital soft tissues are within normal limits.the visualized portions of the temporomandibular joints are within normal limits.the visualized parts of the middle ear cavities and anterior aspects of the mastoid air cells are also well aerated.

text: as before, there has been a bifrontal craniotomy.the previously seen pneumocephalus has resolved, but there are now fluid collections overlying both frontal lobes, which may be postoperative in nature.as before, there is a mesh device over the roof the ethmoid sinuses for repair of the site of a prior encephalocele.there has been significant improvement in the previously seen opacification of the left nasal cavity, which is now well aerated with the exception of soft tissue opacity anteriorly in the ethmoid air cells on the left.the sphenoid sinuses have markedly improved, and are now completely aerated.as before, there are thick mucosal changes in the left maxillary sinus, mildly improved.the right maxillary sinus is well aerated.there is again noted a soft tissue mass along the left nasal ala, which by a prior reports, as well as notes represents a known hemangioma.again seen are permeative bony destructive changes involving the walls of the left maxillary sinus, not significantly changed.note is made of extensive calcification of the cavernous carotid arteries.
summary: significant improvement of paranasal sinus as well as left nasal cavity disease as described above.numerous postoperative changes with resolution of pneumocephaly but now there is fluid overlying both frontal lobes.other findings as above in the body of the report.

text: the study is compared with the recent nect of the head, dated ___.as on that study, there is circumferentially lobulated mucosal thickening involving both maxillary antra, with probable small mucous retention cysts in their floors, with no fluid level.circumferential mucosal thickening involves the maxillary ostia, bilaterally; however, the large- caliber ostiomeatal complexes are patent, bilaterally (is there a history of previous nasal-antral windows and inferior partial ethmoidectomy?).there is extensive soft tissue opacification of left more than right anterior ethmoid air cells, as well as the fronto-ethmoidal recesses, with near-complete opacification of both frontal sinuses, with hyperattenuating contents in, particularly, the right frontal air cell.circumferential mucosal thickening also involves both maxillary sinuses, with fluid levels dorsally fluid appears to layer dependently in the nasopharynx with "trapped" air bubbles; some of these findings may relate to dependent positioning and intubation (though the patient is not intubated at this time).note that the petrous apices are pneumatized, with a small fluid level in the left petrous apex air cell, not clearly present on the ___ study.very limited included anterior portion of the brain demonstrates asymmetric prominence of the right frontal extra-axial csf space, without definite hemorrhage.there is apparent interval clearing of the subarachnoid hemorrhage within the dorsal aspect of the right sylvian fissure and adjacent cortical sulci.
summary: extensive pansinus inflammatory changes, particularly involving the frontal sinuses, bilaterally, with hyperdense contents, on the right; while this may represent inspissated secretions, fungal colonization is another concern.fluid levels in the sphenoid sinuses, bilaterally, which, in this context with layering fluid in the posterior nasopharynx, may, in part, relate to supine positioning.fluid layering within the pneumatized left petrous apex, not definitely present on the ___ ct; again, while this may relate to positioning, infectious petrous apicitis cannot be excluded.very limited depiction of the brain with enlarged bifrontal extra-axial csf space, unchanged since ___, but new since the ___ admission study.there has been apparent interval clearing of the right frontal subarachnoid hemorrhage.minimal induration in the right periorbital soft tissues, with no evidence of intraconal (post-septal) process.

text: there is moderate to marked increase in soft tissue in the frontal sinuses.there is near complete opacification of the ethmoid sinuses.there is moderate to marked thickening of the maxillary sinuses.there is also moderate to marked thickening of the sphenoid sinus.there is no definite evidence of bone destruction.there is some increased density in the maxillary sinus consistent with the history of fungal sinusitis.it could also reflect hemorrhage or increased protein.

text: there is opacification of the left maxillary sinus with interruption in the walls both medially, superiorly, and laterally consistent with the history of mucocele.there is minimal thickening of the right maxillary sinus.there is moderate thickening of the left frontal sinus.there is mild soft tissue thickening of the anterior and central ethmoid cells.there is mild thickening of the inferior aspect of the right side of the sphenoid sinus.the nasal septum is midline.there is irregularity of the medial maxillary wall on the right together with the inferior wall of the ethmoid sinus.there is also some interruption of the ethmoid inferior wall on the left consistent with previous surgery.clinical correlation advised.the sphenoidal septum inserts on the right carotid groove.

text: the frontal sinus is nearly completely opacified bilaterally without definite fracture.multiple comminuted fractures are seen within the nasal bones bilaterally, with lateral displacement of the left bony fragment.there is scattered moderate to severe opacification of bilateral ethmoid air cells.the right lamina papyracea is fractured with lateral displacement of the proximal fracture fragment into the right orbit.a fracture through the inferior right orbit demonstrates a superiorly displaced 3-mm bony fragment.a nondisplaced fracture through the inferior left orbit is seen at the lateral aspect of the infraorbital groove.a fracture through the anterior aspect of the right maxillary sinus is slightly posteriorly displaced by 1 mm.multiple additional fractures involving the right maxillary sinus are seen at the anterolateral, lateral, medial, and posterior margins.the right maxillary sinus is nearly completely opacified.a fracture through the posterior aspect of the left maxillary sinus demonstrates anterior displacement of the lateral fracture fragment.there is a moderately large air-fluid level in the left maxillary sinus.the left malar bone is fractured.there are comminuted fractures involving the lateral wall of the right orbit and separation of the right zygomaticofacial suture.a fracture through the free portion of the right zygomatic bone is non-depressed.both lateral pterygoid processes are fractured in multiple places.small air-fluid levels are noted in bilateral sphenoid sinuses.no fluid is noted within the mastoid air cells.no skull base fracture is detected.the cribiform paltes appear intact bilaterally.extensive edema is noted within the facial soft tissues, including bilateral eyelids.there is a 15 x 11 mm hematoma directly inferior to the right orbit.

text: there are extensive facial fractures involving all aspects of the left maxillary sinus, orbital floor, lateral wall and roof, extending across the sphenoid bone including the sinus and left-sided pterygoid plates and terminating in a right longitudinal temporal bone fracture.large amounts of probable hemorrhage are identified in the paranasal sinuses.the globes appear intact.small amounts of retrobulbar air are noted on the left.the lateral orbital wall fractures impress upon the lateral rectus muscle.no large orbital hematomas are identified, and there is no evidence of entrapment.there is fracture extension through the right carotid canal.there is blood in the right middle and external ear.fracture extends in close proximity to the ossicles.small amounts of pneumocephalus are noted, in proximity to what is likely a hairline left orbiital roof fracture.

text: compared to the prior examination of ___, there has been minimal improvement.there is slight improvement in the amount of opacification of the right maxillary sinus.however, majority of the maxillary sinus remains opacified.the extensive mucosal thickening and small air fluid level within the left maxillary sinus appears approximately unchanged.however, there appears to be minimally improved aeration of the ethmoid and sphenoid sinuses.areas of extensive mucosal thickening remain.the frontal sinuses remain completely opacified.no osseous erosions are present.the increased air within the left nasolacrimal duct remains present.the extraconal air along the lamina papyracea has resolved.in addition, there is lucency within the left pedicle and near the facet of the c3 vertebral body.this could also represent a focus of multiple myeloma.an additional lucent focus is also noted in the right lamina of c3.these areas were not previously imaged.the mastoid air cells are well pneumatized.

text: correlation is made to the concurrent ct of the head as well as a ct of the cervical spine from the same date.multiple minimally displaced fractures of the left frontal bone are seen.these right maxillary sinus.comminuted fractures of the nasal septum are present.comminuted fractures of the nasal bone and the nasal processes of the zygoma bilaterally are noted.there are fractures summary: severe comminuted fractures involving the mid face, orbits bilaterally, left frontal bone, skull base, and left temporal bone.fracture line crossing the left internal carotid artery canal.non-visualization of the left ossicular chain.consider ossicular disurption, as well as extensive hemotympanum.inferior and medial herniation of the left orbital contents as well as disruption of the left orbital apex concerning for injury to the left optic nerve.extensive subarachnoid, intraventricular, and subdural hemorrhages.for full description of these findings, please refer to the concurrent ct of the head.

text: the visualized paranasal sinuses are clear except for very mild mucosal thickening in both maxillary sinuses.there is no evidence for bony erosion.the ostiomeatal units are patent.there is pneumatization of the right clinoid process.there is nasal septal deviation to the right.

text: consistent with the recent ct scan of the head, there is a large air-fluid level in the left sphenoid sinus, which is nearly completely opacified.this also demonstrates predominantly dependent amorphous hyperdense material.there is no evidence of associated bony destruction.the right sphenoid sinus also demonstrates lobulated mucosal thickening and near complete opacification.the right maxillary antrum demonstrates lobulated mucosal thickening without an air fluid level.a large lobulated density is demonstrated within the left maxillary sinus, consistent with a mucus retention cyst along with associated minor mucosal thickening.scattered opacified ethmoid air cells are demonstrated.the frontal sinus is well aerated.the right ostiomeatal unit is patent.the left ostiomeatal unit appears narrowed due to mucosal thickening.the nasal sinus septum is midline.the lamina papyracea are intact.a single right sphenoid sinus septum inserts near the right carotid groove.
summary: opacification and air-fluid level in the sphenoid sinus, most consistent with sinusitis.dependent hyperdense material within the left sphenoid likely represents inspissated secretions in the setting of chronic sinusitis though fungal colonization is another possibility.there is no evidence of bone destruction or superimposed transpacial process.results were discussed by telephone with dr.___ on ___.

text: there is an ng tube within the left nasal passage.the right maxillary sinus has some mucosal thickening at its floor.no maxillary air fluid levels are noted.the ostiomeatal complexes are patent bilaterally with minimal narrowing at their infundibula, due to minimal mucosal thickening.there are scattered areas of minimal mucosal thickening in the ethmoid air cells.there is a small rounded area of polypoid mucosal thickening or a small mucous retention cyst in the left frontal sinus.no air-fluid levels are noted.the sphenoid sinus demonstrates soft tissue opacity posterior with a defect in its floor.there are some areas of bone thickening.these findings are consistent with the patient's prior transsphenoid pituitary adenoma resection.the sella is poorly visualized.a mri with gadolinium would be needed to exclude a pituitary adenoma.however, the suprasellar cistern does appear patent.there is some mild soft tissue density in the left side of the sella which is indeterminate in origin, as noted on the accompanying head ct, there is ventriculomegaly, a right frontal ventriculostomy catheter, and intraventricular and subarachnoid hemorrhage bilaterally.the cribriform plates are at the same levels bilaterally.there is minimal pneumatization of the crista galli.the optic struts are not pneumatized.the nasal septum is midline.
summary: no air fluid levels to indicate acute sinusitis.the ostiomeatal complexes are patent bilaterally.post-surgical changes in the sphenoid sinus sella.given the lack of prior examinations, a mri would be needed to exclude a pituitary adenoma recurrence.please refer to the accompanying head ct for descriptions of the intracranial hemorrhage and ventriculomegaly.dr.___ ___ ___

text: the patient is intubated, with a nasogastric tube.there is mucosal thickening involving all of the paranasal sinuses, with more confluent opacification of the ethmoid sinuses.this could be seen in an intubation.visualized portions of the mastoid air cells are clear.there is soft tissue swelling about the orbits particularly on the right side.there is no evidence of fracture, dislocation or bony destruction.a small left-sided subdural hematoma is present, but not fully evaluated on these images.correlation with head ct is recommended.visualized soft tissues are unremarkable.

text: there is near complete opacification of the left maxillary sinus.the left omu is completely opacified.there is complete opacification of a few of the posterior right ethmoid air cells as well as scattered middle ethmoid air cells bilaterally.there are mild areas of mucosal thickening within both sphenoid sinuses, with moderate-to-large air-fluid level in the left.there are small amounts of mucosal thickening within the left frontal sinus with moderate amounts of mucosal thickening in the right maxillary sinus.there are also some aerosolized secretions in the right frontal sinus.there are no osseous erosions.the nasal septum is midline with a moderate sized leftward and bony spur.the ostiomeatal complex on the right is patent.there has been a prior right nasal bone fracture.visualized portion of the brain are normal.

text: the frontal sinuses are clear.there is opacification of an anterior ethmoid cell or bulla on the left unchanged from previous examination.the maxillary sinuses are clear.the sphenoid sinuses are clear.nasal septum deviates slightly to the left.the ostiomeatal units are patent.there is a ___ bullosa of the right middle turbinate.the cribriform plates are symmetric in height.the anterior clinoids are pneumatized bilaterally.the sphenoid septum inserts on the right carotid groove.
