summary: status post orif of multiple left-sided facial fractures, as described above.

text: the soft tissue swelling in the right buccal space has slightly decreased since the prior study.given the lack of intravenous contrast, a focal abscess in this area cannot be excluded.more inferiorly, dental artifact obscures evaluation.there is enlargement of the distal aspect of the right stensen's duct without evidence of obstructing stone, which is likely due to surrounding inflammation.the previously noted subcutaneous emphysema has resolved.the periorbital soft tissue swelling on the right is improved.there is no evidence of post-orbital abnormality.the air tracking along the superficial layer of the deep cervical fascia on the right seen on the original study from ___ has resolved.the paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are clear.no osseous abnormalities.there is a large amount of dental artifact.this study did not image below the level of the maxilla, and therefore the patient can return for this additional imaging free of charge.
summary: improving inflammatory changes in the right face as described above.due to lack of intravenous contrast, an abscess cannot be entirely excluded, particularly in the buccal space where there is residual inflammatory change.the patient can return at no additional cost for imaging of the lower face.findings were discussed with dr.___ ___ on ___.

text: the paranasal sinuses are clear, without evidence of mucosal thickening or osseous erosion.left anterior clinoid processes are pneumatized.bilateral omcs are patent.cribriform plates are intact with bilateral ___ type 2 fovea ethmoidalis.the lamina papyracea is intact.previously noted subcutaneous emphysema and swelling of the right preseptal and maxillary area has resolved.there is an irregular-shaped enhancing soft tissue anterior to the alveolar ridge on the right measuring approximately 2.4 x 1.5 cm, which could represent scar tissue or inflammatory tissue such as phlegmon.no drainable abscess is identified, however, evolving or developing abscess cannot be totally excluded.the osseous structure is unremarkable.
summary: clear paranasal sinuses.resolution of subcutaneous emphysema on the right.enhancing irregular- shaped soft tissue anterior to the right alveolar ridge.the possibilities include scar tissue or inflammatory tissue.no frank drainable abscess is identified, however, close continued followup with clinical correlation or further evaluation by mri is recommended.the findings are discussed with dr.___ on the day of the study.

text: the sinuses are clear.the ostiomeatal units are clear.the soft tissues are normal.the orbits are normal.the visualized portions of the brain are normal.
summary: no evidence for infection.

text: there has been a substantial interval decrease in subcutaneous emphysema of the right face.a small amount of preseptal, right cheek and right deep neck emphysema still remains.persistent fat stranding and persistent thickening of the platysmus muscle is seen on the right.inflammatory changes are present in the right buccal tissues.there are several scattered small lymph nodes.no abscesses are seen.there has been no interval change in minimal mucosal thickening in the right sphenoid sinus.
summary: interval improvement in right face soft tissue emphysema with persistent inflammatory changes of the right cheek and buccal tissues.no abscesses.

text: there is a non-displaced fracture through the right zygoma.no other acute facial fractures are identified.mucosal thickening seen within the ethmoid and frontal, ethmoid and sphenoid sinuses.right greater than left mucosal thickening also seen in the maxillary sinuses, with likely aerosolized secretions in the right maxillary sinus.intracranial hemorrhage is better evaluated on head ct performed earlier the same day.
summary: nondisplaced right zygomatic fracture.sinus disease, as described.intracranial hemorrhage is better evaluated on concurrent head ct.

text: there is minimal mucosal thickening in the inferior aspect of both maxillary sinuses with a small 8-mm retention cyst along the lateral aspect of the left maxillary sinus.the ethmoid air cells, frontal air cells, and sphenoid air cells are clear.the ostiomeatal complexes are patent bilaterally.there has been extraction of ___ teeth# 7, 8, and 9.periodontal disease is noted surrounding ___# 10 and 11 with irregularity of the ___# 10 tooth.there has been prior root canal apparently or other endodontic procedure of tooth# 10.no definite periapical lucency is visualized, however.fillings are noted in all of the remaining teeth.incidental note is made of an incisive canal cyst.the soft tissues appear unremarkable without evidence of soft tissue abscess or fat stranding.
summary: no definite evidence of periapical abscess.periodontal disease surrounding ___ teeth# 10 and 11.

text: there is no evidence of depressed fracture.large left frontal and periorbital hematoma noted with preseptal thickening.globes and intra-orbital structures appear intact.minimal mucosal thickening is present within the maxillary and ethmoid sinuses.
summary: large left frontal/peri-orbital hematoma.no evidence of acute fracture.

text: there is a destructive aggressive appearing osseous lesion at the body of the right mandible.the cortex is eroded with evidence of pathological fracture at this level.gas locules are seen within this area of bone destruction concerning for infection.no iv contrast was administered which limits the evaluation, however, no discrete fluid collection is identified.diffuse demineralization of the mandible is noted.minimal mucosal thickening of both maxillary sinus, ethmoid, sphenoid, and right frontal sinus.the lamina papyracea is intact.the right ostiomeatal complex appears open, the left is occluded.
summary: destructive lesion at the right mandibular body with associated fracture.findings are most concerning for osteomyelitis (given the presence of gas) though aggressive tumor is also a consideration.clinical correlation is recommended.sinus disease with occluded left omu.findings were discussed with ed resident at the time of the interpretation.

text: there is extensive swelling and hemorrhage in the right frontal scalp and periorbital soft tissues.no orbital or facial fracture is identified.the globe is intact and the lens is in normal position.the intraconal fat is normal in appearance.there is no orbital emphysema or fluid in the right maxillary sinus.the included mastoid air cells and middle ear cavity are clear.there is moderate multifocal subarachnoid hemorrhage as described in the separate dictation of the concurrent ct head.
summary: marked right frontal scalp and periorbital soft tissue hematoma with intact right globe, lens and orbital cone; no orbital fracture.moderate bifrontal subarachnoid hemorrhage (please see separately dictated ct head report).

text: there has been interval craniotomy through the frontal bone and frontal sinuses with surgical fixation plates overlying various craniotomy fragments yielding near anatomic alignment of the frontal bone and frontal sinuses.there is a moderate amount of pneumocephalus and subcutaneous emphysema, all consistent with post-surgical changes.there is a small left frontal subdural hematoma, slightly larger than prior ct studies from ___, ___.there is mild ethmoid sinus mucosal thickening and small right maxillary sinus mucoid retention cyst.the remaining visualized paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are clear.
summary: post-reconstruction of right frontal bone with near anatomic alignment.post- surgical pneumocephalus and subcutaneous emphysema.left small frontal subdural hematoma is slightly larger compared to prior study.

text: comminuted left nasal bone fracture is again redemonstrated.the oribits and sinuses are intact without evidence of fracture.the left maxillary sinus is completely opacified.mucosal thickening is seen within the sphenoid, frontal and right maxillary sinuses.the mastoid air cells remain normally aerated.leftward deviation of the nasal septum with secondary osseous spurring is redemonstrated.
summary: chronic depressed left nasal bone fracture, unchanged from ___.

text: expected post-surgical findings of multiple facial fractures are noted.metallic mesh over the anterior right maxillary sinus and orbital floor are noted.multiple metallic pins are noted along the lateral orbital margins bilaterally.a fixation plate with multiple screws crossing a healing left mandibular ramus fracture is present.the paranasal sinuses are clear with no air fluid levels.there is complete opacification of the right mastoid air cells.there is irregular surface contour of the mandibular condyles bilaterally, which are correctly oriented within the temporomandibular joints.there is no evidence of osseous fusion/ankylosis, however this ct study cannot exclude fibrous ankylosis.there is no evidence of acute fracture.incidental note is made of mild torus mandibularis.
summary: status post multiple facial fractures with expected post-surgical repair changes as described above.no evidence of bony fusion of the temporomandibular joints.irregular contour of mandibular condyles well seated within the temporomandibular joints.however, no areas of lucency or abnormal sclerosis to suggest acute fracture or osteonecrosis.cannot exclude fibrous ankylosis of the temporomandibular joint.if further clinical concern persists, an mri of this region is more sensitive for this evaluation.

text: noncontrast ct sinus with coronal and sagittal reformats.there is minimal mucosal thickening of the left and right maxillary sinuses.the rest of the imaged paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are well aerated.the ostiomeatal units are patent bilaterally.anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.extensive degenerative changes are noted in the upper cervical spine.there are calcifications in the internal carotid arteries.
summary: reported palatal mass is not evaluated on this non-contrast enhanced study.consider gadolinium-enhanced mr ___ ___ is required.sesha

text: no prior studies are available for comparison.the globes, optic nerves, and other orbital contents appear normal.there are no masses at the orbital apices.there are extensive calcifications of the carotid siphons bilaterally.there is deformity of the anterior wall of the left maxillary sinus, likely from prior trauma.the medial walls of the maxillary sinuses are absent, which may be post-surgical change.there is minimal mucosal thickening of the maxillary sinuses bilaterally as well as moderate mucosal thickening of the sphenoid sinus, the right frontal sinus and the frontal ethmoidal recess.there is sclerosis of the walls of the right sphenoid air cell, suggestive of chronic sinusitis changes.the visualized intracranial structures appear grossly normal.
summary: normal orbits and no abnormalities of the orbital apices.however, mri would provide better evaluation of this region.paranasal sinus changes as described above.

text: comparison is made to a head ct from ___.there is minimal mucosal thickening involving the maxillary sinuses bilaterally.the omus bilaterally are patent.previously seen soft tissue change of the right sphenoid air cell has completely resolved.the sphenoid sinus is multipartite and one of the septa inserts upon the right optic nerve canal.there is pneumatization of the left pterygoid recess.the ethmoid and frontal sinuses are clear.bilateral agger nasi cells are seen.there is a left ___ bullosa.the nasal septum is mildly deviated to the right and there is a right-sided nasal septal spur.the cribriform plates are symmetric.the mastoid air cells and middle ear cavities are clear.no suspicious bony abnormalities are noted.cataract surgical changes of the globes are seen bilaterally.the orbits are otherwise normal.there are extensive white matter hypodensities supratentorially not significantly changed from the prior study consistent with chronic microangiopathic changes.multiple old lacunar infarcts of the cerebellar hemispheres are seen bilaterally.
summary: minimal mucosal thickening of the maxillary sinuses.the sphenoid sinus is clear with resolution of the previously seen soft tissue change of the right sphenoid air cell.

text: there is complete opacification of the left maxillary sinus with opacification of the left ostiomeatal unit, left anterior ethmoidal air cells as well as left frontal sinus.as seen on prior mr, there appears to be a site of potential abnormal communication involving the posterior aspect of the left frontal sinus with the extra-axial space (series 2, image 52).additionally, there is mild mucosal thickening of the left sphenoid sinus as well as the right maxillary and anterior ethmoidal air cells.there is also mild mucosal thickening of the right frontal sinus.the right ostiomeatal unit appears to be patent.the cribriform plates are intact.the anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.again seen is hypodensity of the frontal lobes bilaterally, along the margins of the falx as well as a hypodensity involving the inferior frontal lobes.however, this is better appreciated on mri of the brain on the same day.
summary: opacification of the left maxillary sinus, left anterior ethmoidal air cells, as well as left frontal sinus, consistent with an obstructive sinusitis.there appears to be a potential site of communication involving the posterior left frontal sinus with the extra-axial space.mild mucosal thickening of the right frontal, right anterior ethmoidal, and right maxillary sinus.hypodensity involving bilateral frontal lobes along the margins of the falx seen on prior mri, without significant change from earlier in the morning.

text: no fracture is identified involving the sinuses or orbits.the globes and intraconal fat is preserved.the visualized paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells remain normally aerated.a moderate-sized right periorbital hematoma is present.et tube and pool secretions within the ___/oropharynx is noted.
summary: no fracture.

text: fracture of the left orbital apex is identified involving the lateral wall of the superior orbital fissure.additionally, fracture is seen involving the posterolateral wall of the left maxillary sinus with involvement of the inferior orbital fissure.the optic nerve appears uninvolved; however, bony fragments are seen adjacent to the lateral rectus muscle posteriorly, which may be complicated by entrapment.there is opacification of the left maxillary sinus.additional note is made of bilateral nasal bone fractures.several non displaced fractures are seen involving the left zygomatic arch.small air-fluid level is noted within the sphenoid and ethmoid sinuses.note is made of bilateral haller cells and a right ___ bullosa.endotracheal and oroenteric tubes are in place.
summary: left orbital apex fracture involving the posterolateral wall of the left superior orbital fissure and posterolateral wall of the left maxillary sinus involving the inferior orbital fissure.small bony fragments are seen adjacent to the posterior aspect of the left lateral rectus muscle for which entrapment may be of concern.fractures of the nasal bones and the left zygomatic arch.

text: again demonstrated is mild ethmoid sinus and bilateral maxillary sinus opacification.there are no fluid levels.there is no evidence to suggest acute sinusitis.there is no evidence of acute bony injury.
summary: no evidence of acute sinusitis.mild ethmoid and maxillary sinus opacification.

text: the previously described linear lucency traversing the right temporal bone longitudinally (2:64) is less conspicuous on the current study and the lack of overt opacification of the surrounding mastoid air cells raises the question as to whether this represents a true fracture.minimal opacification of a few mastoid air cells is noted, however.there is extensive soft tissue deformity of the right ear with associated hematoma consistent with known laceration with external auditory canal fluid likely representing hematoma.the right middle ear cavity contains small amount of fluid though the malleus and incus appear in normal configuration.small foci of air in the right infratemporal fossa posteriorly are likely related to soft tisse laceration.the left mastoid air cells and middle ear cavity appear well aerated.opacification within a right sphenoid air cell is re-identified with question of an equivocal buckle defect in the inferolateral portion of the sinus; however, the inferior orbital fissure fat appears clean without evidence of hematoma.mucosal thickening within the ethmoid air cells and maxillary sinuses is noted bilaterally.there is atherosclerotic calcification of the cavernous carotids bilaterally.known intraventricular hemorrhage is noted with blood now identified within the lateral and fourth ventricles; no hydrocephalus.orbital structures are intact.nasal bones are intact.
summary: longitudinal linear lucency through right temporal bone may represent a subtle nondisplaced fracture, though the lack of significant opacification of mastoid air cells raises doubt.extensive soft tissue swelling and hematoma related to right ear laceration as described.opacification of right sphenoid sinus, likely representing blood, with equivocal buckle deformity of inferolateral aspect of the sinus wall.intraventricular hemorrhage better evaluated on accompanying head ct.

text: comparison is made to a concurrent head ct.there are comminuted fractures involving the anterior walls of the maxillary sinuses bilaterally with depression of bony fragments especially on the right side.these fractures on the right extend into the infraorbital canal.there is extension of these fractures bilaterally to the inferior orbital rims.comminuted fractures of the posterolateral walls of the maxillary sinuses are seen bilaterally with medial displacement of some of these fracture fragments.blood and fluid are seen filling the maxillary sinuses bilaterally, worse on the right side.fracture through the lateral wall of the right orbit is seen.there is no herniation of orbital contents.minimal if any intraorbital hemorrhage is seen.there appears to be a nondisplaced fracture involving the right parietal and temporal bone which more superiorly appears to cross the groove of the right middle meningeal artery.no associated epidural hematoma is seen, however.there are comminuted fractures of the right zygomatic arch and a nondisplaced fracture of the left zygomatic arch.fracture of the lateral plate of the left pterygoid process is seen.there is a transversely oriented fracture extending through the right vestibule.there is fluid/soft tissue density filling the right middle ear cavity.the fracture appears to extend along the floor of the right middle cranial fossa.there is near-complete opacification of the ethmoid air cells and air-fluid levels within the sphenoid sinus.the nasal septum is deviated to the right.there is fluid/soft tissue density filling the left middle ear cavity as well as the mastoid antrum and some of the remaining mastoid air cells.the left mastoid air cells are small, suggestive of prior inflammation.there is diffuse soft tissue swelling and edema of the entire face including the periorbital regions.endotracheal tube and two orogastric tubes are in place.
summary: transverse fracture through the right temporal bone with the fracture cleft running through the vestibule.comminuted fractures of the anterior and posterolateral walls of the maxillary sinuses bilaterally.fractures of the inferior orbital rims and the lateral wall of the right orbit.no evidence of herniation of orbital contents nor intraorbital hemorrhage.fractures of the zygomatic arches bilaterally and the left pterygoid plate.fracture of the right parietal and temporal bone which crosses the groove of the middle meningeal artery more superiorly but without associated epidural hematoma.please see the concurrent ct of the head for additional findings.

text: again note is made of extensively comminuted fractures of the facial bones.the comminuted fractures involving nasal bones as well as bilateral maxillary spines.there are anterior wall comminuted fractures of the maxillary sinuses bilaterally, with depression, measuring approximately 8 mm on the right and minimal displacement on the left.the bilateral maxillary sinuses as well as nasal cavity and ethmoid and sphenoid sinuses are filled with hemorrhagic fluid and air.the nasal septum is also fractured with comminution, and deviated to the left.the right maxillary sinus posterolateral wall fracture has severe displacement, and extends all the way to the right maxillary alveolar ridge.there are bilateral inferior orbital wall fractures with depression, measuring 4 mm on the right and 3 mm on the left, with herniation of the intraorbital fat and soft tissue, however, there is no muscular herniation.the left infraorbital canal appears involved by the fracture.there is a comminuted fracture of the lateral wall of the right orbit.the septum and walls of the ethmoid sinuses are also fractured, and right medial wall of the orbital wall as well as lamina papyracea appears to be involved in this extensive fracture.there are bilateral nondisplaced fractures versus sutures of the zygomatic arches.the frontal sinuses are also opacified.there is soft tissue swelling centered at the nose extending to the periorbital area bilaterally.there is no hematoma in the retrobulbar location.
summary: extensively comminuted fractures of the nasal bones, maxillary spines, as well as bilateral anterior walls of maxillary sinuses and the posterolateral wall of the right maxillary sinus, ethmoid septum and walls, and bilateral infraorbital walls as well as fractures through the right medial and lateral orbital walls.herniation of orbital fat inferiorly.

text: nasogastric and endotracheal tubes are seen in place, their tips not visualized.since the prior study, there has been increased mucosal thickening within the maxillary sinuses, left greater than right.there is mild mucosal thickening within the sphenoid and ethmoid sinuses.the frontal sinuses are well aerated.there is opacification of several petrous apex air cells.the visualized mastoid air cells are well aerated.the right ostiomeatal complex is patent with mild narrowing of the left omc by soft tissue density.the nasal septum is midline.the cribriform plates are equal in height.the nasal septum is midline.bilateral lamina papyracea are intact.the anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.the included brain, orbits and soft tissues of the superior most neck are within normal limits.
summary: interval worsening of mucosal thickening involving the bilateral maxillary sinuses.no air fluid levels identified.

text: there is extensive periorbital preseptal edema and soft tissue subcutaneous swelling, right greater than left.multiple, predominantly right-sided, facial fractures are identified.there is a comminuted fracture involving the right lateral orbital wall at the sphenozygomatic suture with overlap of a 6 mm.there is a comminuted fracture involving the medial orbital wall with displacement medially and associated surrounding hemorrhage there is a comminuted fracture involving the inferior orbital wall with minimal displacement of orbital contents.the inferior rectus muscle assumes a rounded configuration suspicious for injury.correlate for clinical evidence of entrapment.the right globe appears intact, although there is relative proptosis compared to the contralateral side.there is no evidence vitreous hemorrhage.there is cresentic high attenuation along the posterior-superior aspect of the right globe (3:25) which could represent a small extra-ocular intraconal hematoma.there is a small nondisplaced fracture of the right nasal bone.there is rightward deviation of the nasal septum, likely chronic.scattered conchae bullosa noted incidently.there is a comminuted fracture involving the right zygomatic arch.there is no impingement on the mandibular coronoid process.the left zygomatic arch is intact.no fracture of ptyerygoid plates noted.there is a comminuted fracture involving the right lateral maxillary wall with displacement of several bony fragments medially within the sinus itself.there is high density material within the sinus consistent with hemorrhage.there is a fracture involving the superior aspect of the lamina papyracea on the right.there is a comminuted fracture of the anterior maxillary wall.no left- sided maxillary sinus fractures are identified.the patient is noted to be status post intubation.there is diastasis of the frontozygomatic suture on the right.
summary: extensive of subcutaneous swelling and periorbital edema, right greater than left.multiple right-sided facial fractures including comminuted fractures of the medial, inferior and lateral orbital walls.the globe appears to be relatively intact, however there is an adjacent retrobulbar hematoma.comminuted fractures involving the right lateral, anterior and medial maxillary sinus wall.minimally displaced right nasal bone fracture.comminuted fracture involving the right zygomatic arch.

text: no acute fracture of the facial bones is identified.the visualized portions of the paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are unremarkable.there is no soft tissue swelling or periorbital edema.
summary: no acute fracture of the facial bones detected.

text: there is a markedly comminuted depressed fracture through the left frontal and parietal bones with 14 mm depression of the fracture fragments and associated diffuse subarachnoid, subdural, extraaxial and intraparenchymal hemorrhage.the fracture line extends through the inner and outer tables of the left frontal sinus, which are depressed as well as the left orbital roof, ethmoid septa and sphenoid sinus.fracture line extends along the course of the right cavernous carotid artery and a cta is strongly recommended.there is large left frontal and periorbital subcutaneous tissue swelling .the left orbit appears to be intact but orbital injury cannot be excluded.there is a comminuted nasal bone fracture extending through the nasal septum but not the nasal spine.there is a fracture through the lateral and anterior walls of the right maxillary sinus.there is a fracture through the right occipital condyle.paranasal sinus opacification and air-fluid levels are secondary to trauma.soft tissue density in the right external auditory canal may represent cerumen.clinically correlate.
summary: depressed left frontal and parietal bone fractures with 14 mm depression of the fracture fragments and extension through the left frontal sinus, ethmoid air cells and sphenoid sinus on the right.the fracture line extends through the right cavernous carotid canal and cta should be performed for further evaluation.comminuted nasal bone fracture.right maxillary sinus fracture.right occipital condyle fracture.please see ct c-spine report for full characterization as well as description of posterior subluxation of the occipital condyles on c1.extensive intraparenchymal, extraaxial and subarachnoid hemorrhage is best described on ct head scan performed on the same day.these findings were discussed with dr.___ on ___.

text: there are extensive facial fractures recently described on the ct examination of ___.there has been interval open reduction and internal fixation of a left inferior orbital fracture with improved anatomic alignment compared to the previous examination.multiple lucencies consistent with underlying fractures are still present and there are several foci of pneumocephalus just adjacent to this area.there has been interval open reduction and internal fixation of bilateral extensive comminuted maxillary fractures.there is overall improved alignment of the lateral, medial and anterior walls of the right maxillary sinus.an inwardly displaced 1 cm thin bony fragment from the lateral wall of the maxillary sinus persists.furthermore, despite fixation of the anterior aspect of the left maxillary wall, a large fragment of bone extending distally from the zygomatic arch to the maxillary bone remains on the left (series 400b, image 58).there is diffuse subcutaneous emphysema overall improved compared to the previous examination.there is complete opacification of the maxillary sinuses bilaterally with high density material consistent with hemorrhage.high density material is also present within the ethmoid air cells.there is mild mucosal thickening of the sphenoid and frontal sinuses, respectively.the orbits appear grossly intact.
summary: extensive facial fractures described specifically in the ct report dated ___.interval open reduction and internal fixation of maxilla, maxillary sinus, nasal and zygoma fractures as described above.improved anatomic alignment compared to recent ct examination.1 cm displaced thin bony fragment noted within the left maxillary sinus and larger fragment of bone noted at the inferior lateral margin of the left maxillary sinus.

text: there is moderate lobulated circumferential mucosal thickening with partial opacification of the right maxillary and frontal sinuses.there is a presumed mucus retention cyst in the right sphenoid sinus.there is mild mucosal thickening of bilateral ethmoid air cells and the left frontal and maxillary sinuses.the ostiomeatal units are occluded, bilaterally.there is mild rightward nasal deviation with a small right-sided nasal spur.the osseous structures are otherwise unremarkable.the limited visualized portion of the brain appears grossly normal.
summary: partial opacification of multiple sinuses, right greater than left, with obstructed omus, consistent with chronic inflammation.no air- fluid level or aerosolized secretions are identified to suggest acute component.

text: there is a markedly comminuted depressed fracture through the right frontal bone with 4 mm depression of the fracture fragments.the fracture line extends to the inner and outer tables of the left frontal sinus and continues through the ethmoid septa and left posterior sphenoid wall.there is also a depressed fracture of the right orbital roof with approximately 6 mm downward depression of osseous fragments posterior to the globe.the bone fragments appear to touch, but not entrap the superior rectus muscle.there is a small amount of post-septal air but no retrobulbar hematoma.the optic nerve appears intact.there is a nondepressed fracture through the left orbital roof.the left orbit and retrobulbar fat appear unremarkable.fracture lines involve the left superior orbital fissure raising concern for injury to the traversing optic nerve.nondisplaced fracture of the left carotid canal is visualized.there are fluid levels in the maxillary and sphenoid sinuses and opacification of numerous ethmoid air cells, likely secondary to hemorrhage.there is a large right frontal subgaleal hematoma containing small pockets of air.trace pneumocephalus is seen adjacent to the cribriform plate.the mastoid air cells appear well aerated.the temporomandibular joints are well seated and no mandibular fracture is seen.
summary: comminuted right frontal bone fracture with 4 mm depression of fracture fragments and extension of the fracture to the right frontal sinus, ethmoid air cells and sphenoid sinus on the left.a fracture line extends through the left optic canal, raising concern for possible injury to the left optic nerve.nondisplaced fracture of the left carotid canal is visualized, cta is recommended if clinically warranted there is a depressed right orbital roof fracture with no evidence of retrobulbar hematoma.this study was reviewed by dr.___ ___.

text: the paranasal sinuses are normally aerated with no mucosal thickening or air-fluid levels identified.the ostiomeatal units are patent.the cribriform plates are intact.the anterior clinoid processes are not pneumatized.laminae papyracea is intact.the nasal septum is deviated to the right with a small bony spur.the cortical margins of the mandibles are well seen without evidence of destruction or erosion.the subjacent fat does not demonstrate any evidence of stranding, increased attenuation, mass or abscess.no the articular surfaces of the temporomandibular joint do not demonstrate any erosion, cortical destruction or evidence of subchondral cysts.
summary: no inflammation, mass or abscess in the fat subjacent to right mandible.mr is a better study to evaluate for osteomyelitis.dr.___ was the supervising radiologist and reviewed the case.

text: there is no evidence of fracture of the facial bones.incompletely included in the field of view is the right occipital bone fracture, previously detailed on the companion head ct report.there is mild mucosal thickening of the bilateral maxillary sinuses as well as ethmoid air cells and sphenoid sinus.polypoid mucosal thickening of the right maxillary sinus is consistent with a mucus retention cyst or polyp.the orbits are unremarkable.no regional soft tissue abnormality is identified.the right ostiomeatal unit is patent.the left ostiomeatal unit is narrowed by mucosal thickening.
summary: no fracture of the facial bones identified.mild pansinus mucosal thickening and small mucus retention cyst or polyp of the right maxillary sinus.

text: there is an oblique nondisplaced fracture through the right frontal bone, which extends through the orbital roof posteriorly to the apex of the orbital cone.the optic nerve is normal in calibaer adn course with clean adjacent fat.the fracture involves the lateral maxillary sinus wall, also in a nondisplaced fashion.there is a minimally displaced fracture of the lateral plate of the right pterygoid.a minimally displaced left nasal bone fracture is also identified.no other fractures are seen.there is extensive preseptal and periorbital subcutaneous emphysema with swelling in the adjacent soft tissues.the globes appear intact.there is no retroorbital hematoma.high- density fluid consistent with hemorrhage fills the maxillary, ethmoid and sphenoid sinuses.pneumocephalus is noted adjacent to the anterior frontal and temporal lobes as well as within the cisterna magna and along the posterior spinal cord.nasogastric and orogastric tube are seen in place.degenerative change is noted in the upper cervical spine.extensive calcification is seen within the cavernous carotid arteries.please refer to the head ct (clip ___) for details regarding brain injury.
summary: minimally displaced right frontal bone fracture extending into the right orbital roof with involvement of the right lateral pterygoid plate.left nasal bone fracture.extensive subcutaneous emphysema and pneumocephalus.the paranasal sinuses are opacified with blood products.

text: there is a comminuted nasal bone fracture involving the nasal septum but not extending to the nasal spine.there is also a fracture of the left first maxillary incisor and minimally displaced fracture through the right maxilla anterior to the first and second incisors.two small osseous fragments are seen in the anterior soft tissues.there are air fluid levels in the maxillary and sphenoid sinuses.there is mild mucosal thickening and scattered air- fluid levels within the ethmoid air cells.fluid is seen within the nasal cavity and ___-oropharynx.the right and left omus are occluded secondary to mucosal secretions.
summary: comminuted nasal bone fracture extending through the nasal septum.fractured left first maxillary incisor.fracture through the right maxilla anterior to the right first and second incisors.two small osseous fragments in the anterior soft tissues.scattered paranasal sinus air-fluid levels and mucosal thickening.findings discussed with dr.___ at the time of dictation.

text: comparison is made to concurrent head ct, cervical spine ct.there are several small areas of subarachnoid hemorrhage along the right frontal lobe.there is also a thin extra-axial hemorrhage along the left frontal temporal region, with a thickness of approximately 0.3 cm, which likely represents a subdural hematoma.please refer to the concurrent ct of the head for additional significant findings.multiple fractures are seen through the left frontal and parietal bones.there is a comminuted fracture of the superolateral aspect of the left orbit.there is diastasis of the left zygomaticofrontal suture.comminuted fracture of the inferior wall of the left orbit is seen posteriorly.comminuted fractures of the posterolateral, inferior, medial, and anterior walls of the left maxillary sinus are seen.there is a nondisplaced fracture through the anterior wall of the right maxillary sinus.fractures are seen extending through the pterygoid plates bilaterally.a fracture of the left hard palate is seen.there is a comminuted fracture of the left parasymphyseal region of the mandible with posterior displacement of the right side of the mandible.fracture along the alveolar ridge is seen extending from the central portion of the mandible to the right body of the mandible.there is also a fracture of the left maxillary alveolar ridge.there are multiple missing teeth, especially the incisors and canines of the maxilla as well as a fracture of the left maxillary premolar.several teeth have dental caries and lucencies surrounding the roots which likely represent scalp and the right cheek.there is large amount of hemorrhage and soft tissue swelling overlying the left orbit with subcutaneous emphysema.there are several high density material within the palpebrae
